<br>
On Friday of last week a bug report was sent to Mythic via the Support email concerning a serious &quot;bug&quot; concerning an upper level trade skill exploit. It is more of a database typo than anything, most likely overlooked when the gold to platinum conversion was changed from 1:100 to 1:1000. On Saturday I followed up with a phone call to the support line and spoke to an individual in depth about the problem. I was assured that my original email had indeed been received and was in the system. Simply to make sure it did get looked at, the person on the phone had entered another ticket under the problem and sent it to the dev team. <br>
<br>
The problem remains unfixed as of today when I logged into Pendragon to see if it had been corrected post-patch. <br>
<br>
Currency in this game is one of the restricting factors in everything that takes place. There appears to be a good balance between making money through slaying monsters and by sitting in town working on trades. Take away that and a serious imbalance will occur. Gold will become worthless, as we have seen with other online games, RvR will eventually become a joke and high level trade skills will become commonplace.<br>
<br>
While creating an excel spreadsheet to make some cost figures easier for myself and my friends to reference, I came across an item that obviously was not converted to the new currency rates in Hibernia. Wether or not this also exists in other realms is not known to me. The Carbide Osnadurtha Hauberk, an item that can be crafted with ~650-675 skill in armorsmithing, costs roughly 87 gold to make. It is a level 6, tier 3 item and should sell from a merchant for roughly 130 gold. It does not, in fact it sells for 1030 gold. <br>
<br>
The exact percentage escapes me right now, but this item would sell back to a vendor at roughly 880 gold resulting in a net profit of roughly 800 gold per piece. Just for the sake of comparison a full suit of the level 8 (diamond) scale osnadurtha can be made for 560 gold. One could power-skill themselves to 'max skill' in anything just from selling a handful of these.<br>
<br>
This erroneous sale value will destroy any economy that exists in Hibernia on every server and give anyone in range of crafting this item a blank check to create hordes of gold. There are a handful of people at this range now on my server already, let alone the others. <br>
<br>
The main question is why hasn't this been fixed? I have been praying each day that I will log in and see it fixed, as each day brings people closer to it. The only recourse I feel I have is to go public with the information and hope it will force Mythic to either 1) fix it immediately or 2) state that the sale value being displayed is simply a bug and it will, in fact, not sell back for a profit.<br>
<br>
If this does remain in the game, DAoC will no longer be worth playing for myself and I am sure many others. Each day of watching this remain uncorrected has deepened a 'why bother' feeling I experienced after I first weighed the repurcussions of letting this remain in the game. <br>
<br>
I would like to encourage people to email Mythic for a statement on this matter and demand that it be fixed immediately. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utyvanstonecrusher.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tyvan Stonecrusher</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/30/01 2:09:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=82.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bug, Baaad Bug, Baaaaad Baaaaaad Bug</span><hr size=1> Wow!  800GP for an item that costs 87GP to make!?!  That can be a problem.  If this is the case, then Mystic really does need to fix this ASAP or the economy in DAoC will suffer greatly!<br>
